      {
        "id": 4352827,
        "name": "John Vizuete",
        "username": "J.Vizuete",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/j.vizuete/{size}/2784_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-04-24T19:35:27.647Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I have a bottle of 17 and would be eager to hear from anyone with experience with this vineyard. Although I generally find 2017 to be a charming and approachable vintage, Roumier seems to need more time than just about anybody else in burgundy. A 17 MSD Bussiere was tight and unyielding last July, so I wasn\u2019t planning on opening mine any time soon. To say nothing of more recent releases\u2026</p>",
        "post_number": 2,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 8,
        "updated_at": "2024-04-24T19:35:27.647Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
