        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-04-25T08:45:26.455Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Combottes is an old river bed/bank, with coarse alluvium over limestone, and the wines are quite round, supple, fleshy and charming. A wine I taste more often from barrel than I drink from bottle, because one doesn\u2019t see it much.</p>",
